House Resolution 575
By: Representative Lupton of the 83rd
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Moving in the Spirit; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Moving in the Spirit was founded in 1986 by Dana Lupton, Leah Mann, and
3 Genene Stewart to empower underserved youth through dance, growing from a single class
4 for 25 girls into an award-winning creative youth development program; and
5 WHEREAS, throughout its 39-year history, Moving in the Spirit has impacted more than
6 5,000 children through its programs and inspired tens of thousands more through workshops
7 and performances, forging key partnerships with organizations such as the Atlanta Children's
8 Shelter, Boys & Girls Clubs of Atlanta, and KIPP Atlanta Schools; and
9 WHEREAS, the organization has earned national recognition, including being honored at a
10 2005 White House ceremony hosted by First Lady Laura Bush and performing for Liberian
11 President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf; and
12 WHEREAS, in 2021, Moving in the Spirit opened a $10 million performing arts center at
13 MARTA's Edgewood/Candler Park development, establishing a permanent home to further
14 its mission of transforming lives through the arts; and
