15 WHEREAS, its measurable impact includes a 96 percent increase in student confidence, with
16 100 percent of seniors graduating high school and pursuing higher education, vocational
17 training, or military service; and
18 WHEREAS, alumni of Moving in the Spirit have gone on to excel in diverse careers,
19 including Broadway, public health, education, and civic leadership, with many attributing
20 their success to the confidence, discipline, and creativity instilled by the program; and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable organization be
22 appropriately honored during this special time.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
24 the members of this body commend Moving in the Spirit for its decades of outstanding
25 contributions to youth development through the arts and extend best wishes for continued
26 success.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
28 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
29 Moving in the Spirit.
